rComments: Yes, the review below is correct. She is a genuine person but if you want to get a good grade you have to make super abstract and unusual arguments about the Cold War... Try to(somehow) prove comic books won the Cold War and you should get at least a B.

She is nice person and a clear lecturer, but my goodness she is a hard grader as she expects complex arguments and unconventional essay stylistic writing. I would recommend her if you want an interesting class but if you want to save your GPA, I do not recommend.

Erica Fraser is probably the best prof ive had in my 4 years of uni! wish i took more class with her. very nice, always there to help you! she really cares for her student which is different from a lot of university professors!

This has been my favourite class (History of he USSR) so far! Professor Fraser is an engaging and clear lecturer, and all of her classes were very interesting. There were a lot of short assignments, but they weren't very difficult and she graded fairly. I definitely recommend taking a course with her!

Far and away the best prof I've had. She's a stimulating lecturer and fair marker, and her enthusiasm for the subject is contagious. There's a hefty amount of reading, but its always interesting -- especially the primary documents. Even in a large class, she encouraged discussion and tried to make genuine connections with students.
Amazing professor. Very knowledgeable on the subject, and I found by only using few powerpoint slides you get to understand the information better. She is great at giving feedback, and reliable.

Probably the best professor I've had yet. Attendance isn't mandatory but the lectures are just from what she's saying, there aren't slides, so you've got to go to class. It's hard, a decent amount of work and plenty of writing, but she's willing to help you however she can. Conveys the material really well and makes it interesting.
